spotted shag
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a mainly South Island coastal variety having white stripes along the sides of its head, and a round black spot on the ends of its wing feathers
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:Environment
Region:[none]
See:
